						<summary>

						<p>Stone in front of the <hi rend="italic">dhvajastambha</hi> in the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Kali-Viṭraju (Vishṇuvardhana V).</p>						

						<p>Registers a gift of land sowable with 4 <hi rend="italic">puṭṭis</hi> of <hi rend="italic">āḍlu</hi> by Kaḍeyarāju, the servant of Vijayāditya. The gift is stated to have been made in the name of Aytakava, the queen of Kali-viṭrāju. In characters of about the 8th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
